{
  "id": "019d327f-132f-77c0-a1cb-bf2825817894",
  "content": "# corvia-adapter-agent-teams: Design Concept\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Status:** Concept / Exploration\n\n## Summary\n\nAn adapter that ingests Claude Code Agent Teams artifacts (team configs, task lists, mailbox messages, teammate session logs) into corvia's knowledge store. This makes Agent Teams' ephemeral coordination state into persistent, searchable organizational memory.\n\n## Motivation\n\nAgent Teams (Claude Code v2.1.32+, experimental) coordinate multiple Claude Code sessions with shared task lists and inter-agent messaging. However:\n\n- All team state is ephemeral. Cleaned up when the team shuts down.\n- No cross-team memory. A new team starts from scratch.\n- No searchable history of what teams discovered, decided, or produced.\n- No temporal queries (\"what did the security review team find last week?\").\n\ncorvia already runs as an MCP server that every teammate loads automatically via `.mcp.json`. The adapter would close the loop by also capturing the team's coordination artifacts.\n\n## Strategic Position\n\nThis adapter positions corvia as \"how you remember what your Agent Teams did.\" Every Claude Code user with Agent Teams gets corvia value. The adapter is a distribution channel for corvia adoption.\n\n## Data Sources\n\n| Source | Location | Content |\n|--------|----------|---------|\n| Team config | `~/.claude/teams/{team-name}/config.json` | Team members, roles, agent IDs |\n| Task list | `~/.claude/tasks/{team-name}/` | Tasks with status, ownership, dependencies |\n| Mailbox | `~/.claude/teams/{team-name}/inboxes/{agent-name}.json` | Inter-agent messages |\n| Session logs | `~/.claude/sessions/*.jsonl` (if session history enabled) | Full tool calls, responses, failures |\n\n## Threat Context\n\nThis adapter is also a defensive move. If Anthropic ships native persistent memory for Agent Teams, corvia's multi-agent knowledge value prop narrows. Being the best Agent Teams knowledge layer now builds adoption before that happens. corvia's moat remains: multi-tool (not just Claude), multi-repo, temporal queries, knowledge graph, and git-as-truth.\n",
